The problem is that the following test now fails:

> class X {
    public String foo
    void set(String name, String value) { }
}
>def x = new X()
x.foo = "2"
assert x.@foo == "2"

I think restoring the code to the way it was pre- 2c226838ed69685 commit and then partially duplicating the map check prior to throwing the `ReadOnlyPropertyException` exception would allow all tests to pass.

